Responses:

What did you find most helpful or most challenging in the video?

I find how they say that we should keep it simple to be the most helpful, and that we wont always get it right always.

What do you find difficult about prayer/meditation?

What I find difficult about prayer is sitting still and focusing on prayer, not everything else in my head that is trying to distract me.

What do you find easy?

I find saying a prayer easy.

Why do you think prayer/meditation can often feel hard?

Because I can't focus on the task at hand.

Pete says the best piece of advice is to “Keep it simple, keep it real and keep it up.”

Keep it simple: “your prayer life is at its best at its simplest”

What is the simple heart of prayer?

KISS

Keep it real: “Don’t role-play before God”

What does this mean?

Don't fake it, keep it real.

Keep it up: “Don’t give up praying too soon”

Do you find it challenging to persevere in prayer/meditation? How can we be encouraged to keep going?

By looking for the light at the end of the tunnel.
